column48: I really like the campaign and had a lot of fun solving the quests, but there is one point which I don't like. Tangleswap was the winner of the test campaign and they got the most SMR tokens for the distribution to the community. That was quite a huge amount of SMR, but only a few people (I think the top 200) got a reward. There were certainly many people like me who put a lot of time into the campaign and made thousands of transactions. It would have been better to split that up by performance, without a limit on the top 200 participants. With 275th place, you're basically left empty-handed.

column48:
For all the progress that is being made, IOTA is miles behind all other crypto projects. I've been with the project since 2017 and if it doesn't finally reach a milestone, I'll be leaving next year. At some point, it must be delivered and I do not mean a test network of a test network but finally a finished product that can finally be used by the advertised dapps. 

IOTA is losing more and more connection. I am very well connected in the community and it is slowly turning into despair among the established people. Coordicide has been promised for years. This keeps the core of members who have been there from the beginning, but if you continue for more than a year without Coordicide, the last remnants of people in the community will be alienated and the project will die.

 I don't understand why tangleswap won, because I tried to use it 4 days and it didn't work.
 I was in several projects every day of the campaign, in the zealy campaigns and I've won about 700 smrs ≈ $40😪 
I honestly expected more
I trust shimmer and iota and we have been able to see progress on the network, waiting for mainnet
